title: For Sale:  NEW Silencerco Spectre II Silencer Suppressor
postcontent: Check us out online!  www.54-17arms.com Brand new Silencerco Spectre II Silencer Suppressor with thread mount. No credit card fees and shipping to your local FFL is FREE!  Price does not include the NFA tax stamp or local sales tax.  Also, with the purchase of this suppressor, we can assist you in creating a basic living trust!  A living trust will speed up the transfer process.  Let us know if you have questions.  With its construction of ultra high performance and tough Stainless Steel, the Spectre II allows weapon fire to go virtually unnoticed. It is not only super tough, but also one of the quietest .22 suppressors known to man. With the Spectre II, users will also enjoy its multi-caliber versatility. The Spectre II has a unique CTA baffle design for easy disassembly and is user serviceable, which is very important for any .22 LR silencer. Because the .22 LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue .22 silencers must be able to be disassembled for cleaning and regularly maintained. Most .22 silencers on the market can be disassembled for cleaning, however they require cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds or often times they will fuse together and they are unable to come apart. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the silencer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the tube, there is simply too much build up of fouling and lead to remove the tube from most .22 LR silencers on the market. The Spectre II has the unique CTA baffle design that keeps the carbon and lead debris from reaching the silencer tube allowing it to be disassembled easily. postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.

title: For Sale:  Post War P.38
postcontent:
For sale :  Walther P.38 . 

  The P.38 was the universal sidearm of the German army in WWII.  After the war the proven 9mm design went back into production by Walther , virtually identical to the WWII model except for the frame being made of alloy.  In it's new incarnation the P.38 was carried by the military and police of virtually all the Eastern Bloc countries.  Thus , this P.38 9mm pistol is a piece of Cold War history.  This particular piece was built by Walther in 1962 , and I could detect virtually no evidence of use when I acquired it.  I have put approx 200 rounds thru it.  The holster is period correct and holds a spare magazine. My asking price of $475 is very reasonable given how clean and tight this pistol is.
